Levain Lemon Cookies (copycat)
  --Sarah Martens

3 c ap flour
1/4 c cornstarch
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 c salted butter, softened
1/2 c shortening
1 c sugar
1/2 c packed brown sugar
1 tbsp lemon zest
1/2 tsp salt
2 large eggs
2 tbsp fresh lemon juice
1 1/2 c lemon-flavored or white chocolate baking chips

In a medium bowl combine flour, cornstarch, and baking soda; set aside. In a large bowl beat butter and shortening with a mixer until creamy. Add sugar, brown sugar, lemon zest, and salt. Beat on medium until very light, 3 min. Scrape bowl; beat in eggs, and lemon juice. Add flour mixture and mix until just combined. Stir in baking chips. Line a tray or cookie sheet with parchment paper. Divide dough into 10 equal portions. Shape dough portions into balls and place on tray. Freeze for 4-24 hr. Adjust oven rack to middle position. Preheat oven to 400F. Arrange half of the dough balls on a parchment-lined cookie sheet. Bake 6 min (do not open oven). Adjust temperature to 350F. Bake until edges are firm and cookies appear set, ~14-15 min more. Transfer to a wire cooling rack; cool completely. Repeat with remaining cookies. 
